## Context

* Astro uses a component system based on server-side rendering by default
* Astro components are Server Components by default (no need for `'use client'`)
* This project uses pure Astro without React, Vue, or other client frameworks
* For client-side interactivity, use inline scripts or Astro components with `client:*` if necessary

## Astro Components (Server Components by default)

Astro components are rendered server-side by default and can:
- Perform database queries directly with Prisma
- Read system files
- Access environment variables via `import.meta.env`
- Use all Node.js APIs
- Use better-auth for authentication

**Example:**
```astro
---
// This code runs server-side only
import { db } from '../lib/db';
import { auth } from '../lib/auth';

const session = await auth.api.getSession({
  headers: Astro.request.headers,
});

const users = await db.user.findMany();
---

<div>
  {users.map((user) => (
    <p>{user.name}</p>
  ))}
</div>
```

## Client-side Interactivity (inline scripts)

For interactivity without frameworks, use inline scripts in Astro components:

```astro
---
// Props and server logic
export function Counter(props: { initialCount?: number }) {
  const count = props.initialCount ?? 0;
  return { count };
}

const { count } = Counter(Astro.props);
---

<div>
  <p id="count-display">Count: {count}</p>
  <button id="increment-btn">Click me</button>
</div>

<script>
  let currentCount = {count};
  const display = document.getElementById('count-display');
  const button = document.getElementById('increment-btn');
  
  button.addEventListener('click', () => {
    currentCount++;
    if (display) {
      display.textContent = `Count: ${currentCount}`;
    }
  });
</script>
```

## Using better-auth in components

```astro
---
import { auth } from '../lib/auth';

// Check authentication server-side
const session = await auth.api.getSession({
  headers: Astro.request.headers,
});

if (!session) {
  return Astro.redirect('/login');
}

const user = session.user;
---

<div>
  <p>Welcome, {user.name || user.email}!</p>
  <form method="POST" action="/api/auth/sign-out">
    <button type="submit">Sign out</button>
  </form>
</div>
```

## Important Rules

1. Astro components are SSR by default - no need for `'use client'`
2. Prefer server-side rendering for performance
3. Use inline scripts for simple interactivity
4. For authentication, use better-auth server-side in components
5. Access environment variables with `import.meta.env.VARIABLE_NAME`
6. Use Prisma for all database queries
